Although Black women are the fastest-growing group of entrepreneurs, they face several barriers when it comes to seeking funding for their ventures.
Despite the odds, Black women business owners are making historic moves in the realm of entrepreneurship.
According to Black Enterprise, a trio of sisters opened the first Black women-owned beauty store in their hometown of Buffalo, New York.
The sisters say their entrepreneurial journey is about increasing the representation of Black women in the beauty industry and they hope their historic milestone inspires others.
